<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL TENNIS / SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' FINALS; SANTA BARBARA WINS 7TH 
CONSECUTIVE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE MCKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Santa Barbara Dons won their seventh consecutive Southern Section Division 
I boys' tennis championship with a 17 2/3-3 1/3 victory over third-seeded Dana 
Hills Wednesday at Knowlwood Tennis Club in Montecito. 
</P>
<P>
 The match was never close as Santa Barbara won five of six first-round 
sets.Santa Barbara (25-0) clinched the match by the second round, leading 12-2 
at one point. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons got three singles victories from senior Nathan Jackmon and freshman 
Adam Webster and also got three victories from the doubles team of Jimmy Walker 
and Ian Carrera and Jason Yardi and Travis Logue. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills finished at 23-1. 
</P>
<P>
 "Playing at home would have helped. But the way we played today wouldn't have 
mattered," said Dana Hills Coach John Stephens. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought our kids might have given them a little too much respect. They 
played like they were intimidated." DAVE MCKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
