<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL TENNIS / SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANA HADDAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calabasas 13 2/3, Santa Ynez 7 1/3 -- The Coyotes (17-4) won their first 
Southern Section championship since 1986 after winning eight of nine doubles 
matches in the Division IV final at Agoura High. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas' No. 1 doubles team of Anapam Mishra and Phil Abramson swept three 
matches, dropping only two games, as did the No. 2 team of Darren Miller and 
Jason Arashaben.  
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas (17-4) won five section titles in six years from 1981-86 in Division 
2-A and 3-A. DANA HADDAD 
</P>
