<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Edison sophomores Kerry O'Bric and Marie Philman, finished one-two in the 
heptathlon competition late Tuesday night at the 16th California high school 
championships at Mt. San Antonio College. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Bric, who finished first in the 100 hurdles (15.8 seconds), 200 meters 
(26.1) and long jump (17 feet 4 inches), had 4,401 points to 4,309 for Philman, 
who won the high jump (5-3), shotput (39-3 3/4) and triple jump (127-0). 
</P>
<P>
 O'Bric will participate in the triple jump and Philman in the discus at the 
State track and field championships this weekend at Cerritos College. 
</P>
<P>
 University's Jennifer Stanton finished sixth among the 45 heptathlon 
competitors with 3,578 points, and Edison's Erin Zimmon was seventh with 3,479. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Stewart said Wednesday he has been hired as the wrestling coach at 
Esperanza. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart has coached University the past two seasons and was 34-7-2. The 
Trojans were 23-2-2 and tied for the Sea View League championship last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart was an assistant under Chuck Bishop at Esperanza for seven years 
before coming to University. Bishop resigned at the end of last season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor's Trent Bryson, the 3,200 meters runner-up at the Sea View 
League track and field championships this season, will attend UC Santa Barbara, 
Newport Harbor Coach Bim Barry said Wednesday. 
</P>
