<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESPITE PLANS, ERHAAB CLOSES TO WIN ENGLISH DERBY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 215th English Derby didn't go according to plan for Erhaab, but he won 
anyway. 
</P>
<P>
 Staying back to avoid trouble in the middle of the race, Erhaab closed with a 
rush in the final 100 yards of the 1 1/2-mile race under 52-year-old Willie 
Carson and won by 1 1/4 lengths Wednesday before some 100,000, including Queen 
Elizabeth II. 
</P>
<P>
 Kings Theater finished second, 1 1/2 lengths ahead of Colonel Collins, with 
Mister Baileys fourth in the field of 25 3-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
 Broadway Flyer, owned by golfer Gary Player, finished 21st. 
</P>
<P>
 "It certainly wasn't the plan," winning trainer John Dunlop said after his 
colt came from far back. "But there was a lot of trouble in the middle of the 
race, and Willie didn't want to get involved. I thought that he was so far back 
he couldn't win from there. He got a lovely ride through (traffic), and then I 
thought we would finish a respectable fourth." 
</P>
</TEXT>
