<P>
BRIEFLY: BUSINESS: REDONDO PIER MAY REOPEN IN JANUARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Redondo Beach municipal pier is on the mend. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials say reconstruction of the Horseshoe Pier, which sustained more than 
$6 million in damage from storms and a fire in 1988, could be finished by the 
end of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 They hope for a reopening celebration in January. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials met with merchants and residents Saturday to give an update on the 
progress of the reconstruction, which began in July. The project is expected to 
cost $11 million. JAMES BENNING 
</P>
