<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENVIRONMENT: BAY CLEANUP HEARINGS SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The public may comment at two public hearings today on a five-year plan to 
clean up Santa Monica Bay, part of the Santa Monica Bay Restoration Project. 
</P>
<P>
 The project, which is administered by the U.S. Environmental Protection 
Agency, affects an area from the Ventura County line to Point Fermin. 
</P>
<P>
 The draft plan, released in April, identifies 73 priority actions that would 
cost an estimated $67 million.  
</P>
<P>
 The first hearing will be at 10 a.m. at the Los Angeles Regional Water Quality 
Control Board, 101 Center Plaza Drive, Monterey Park. Those who cannot attend 
may send written comments to Karen Caesar at that address. The comments must be 
received by June 15. 
</P>
<P>
 A second meeting will be at 6 p.m. in the IRI Room of the Veterans Memorial 
Building, 4117 Overland Ave., Culver City. 
</P>
