<TEXT>
<P>
 The public will have its last opportunity to comment on the Palos Verdes 
Library District's 1994-95 budget at a board meeting June 9. 
</P>
<P>
 The library board plans to report on proposals to reduce the cost of furniture 
for the Peninsula Center Library from $1.2 million to $820,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The community group Save Our Libraries recently criticized the district for 
being extravagant in a time when budgets have been cut to keep the peninsula's 
three libraries open. 
</P>
