<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SANTA MONICA; QUAKE DAMAGE FORCES PHARMACY TO MOVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For 50 years, three generations of the Litvak family have run the Santa Monica 
Homeopathic Drug Co. out of the same narrow storefront on 4th Street. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Jan. 17 earthquake damaged the building so severely that it will be 
under repair for up to six months. So the Litvaks, their shelves overcrowded 
with doses of animal, vegetable and mineral substances even before the quake, 
have moved. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've really outgrown the spot, and earthquake repairs made (the move) 
necessary," said Bob Litvak. His parents, Norman and Mary, both 82, own the 
pharmacy, one of the nation's oldest and busiest specializing in homeopathic 
remedies. 
</P>
<P>
 The new store at 629 Broadway opened Wednesday. KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
