148 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY COVER STORY; 3 PASADENA GROUPS HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Pasadena neighborhood associations won awards during last weekend's 
Neighborhoods USA Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena's Bungalow Heaven Neighborhood Assn. took top honors in the physical 
needs category for restoring its neighborhood park.Members of the association 
eliminated drug and gang activity at McDonald Park, where children now can play 
safely. 
</P>
<P>
 The Navarro Avenue-Tremont Howard Assn. placed second in the social needs 
category for its public safety project. The association encourages youth to 
participate in the community and promotes friendship and civic pride among 
residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jefferson Park Neighborhood Assn. earned an honorable mention for its park 
and neighborhood safety program. The association's goal is to preserve and 
develop the safety of Jefferson Park and the surrounding neighborhood and to 
enhance the aesthetic and recreational value of the park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
