METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SAN FERNANDO; 3.7 
AFTERSHOCK RATTLES RESIDENTS OVER WIDE AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A magnitude 3.7 aftershock of the Northridge quake rumbled through the Los 
Angeles metropolitan area Wednesday night, rattling china cupboards and 
startling thousands of residents but apparently causing no injuries or major 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
 The aftershock, which struck at 8:27 p.m., was centered about a mile southwest 
of the city of San Fernando, according to Caltech seismologist Riley Geary. The 
temblor was felt throughout the San Fernando Valley, in Downtown Los Angeles, 
Hollywood and the Santa Monica and Venice areas. 
</P>
<P>
 Seismologists said there have been more than 8,000 substantial aftershocks of 
the devastating Jan. 17 quake. 
</P>
