<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: SANTA ANA VALLEY TO PLAY CRENSHAW IN BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Santa Ana Valley High School boys' basketball team will play a 
home-and-home series with two-time State Division I champion Los Angeles 
Crenshaw, Falcon Coach Rich Prospero said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons will play at Crenshaw next season.Crenshaw will play at Santa Ana 
Valley during the 1995-96 season. It will be the first time Crenshaw has played 
a non-tournament game in Orange County, according to Cougar Coach Willie West. 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw, which has won six State titles, defeated Carmichael Jesuit, 89-79, 
to win the State title this season. The Cougars defeated Jesuit, 73-66, in 
1993. Crenshaw has defeated Mater Dei in the Southern California Regional final 
the past two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley, led by All-Orange County guard Olujimi Mann, lost to La 
Crescenta Crescenta Valley, 69-67, in the Southern Section I-AA semifinals this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons also will play in the Raleigh (N.C.) News and Observer tournament 
next season. CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
