ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; WOMAN, 35, KILLED IN AUTO ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 35-year-old woman was killed late Tuesday when her car collided with a 
pickup truck, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred at Trabuco Road and Yale Avenue about 10:45 p.m., police 
Lt. Sam Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chu-saw Hsia of Irvine was taken to Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, where 
she died. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the pickup, a 26-year-old Marine stationed at the El Toro Marine 
Corps Air Station, was not injured, but a passenger in the truck sustained 
minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Hsia's car was traveling west on Trabuco and the pickup was 
heading south on Yale when the collision occurred. 
</P>
<P>
 "Someone ran a red light," Allevato said. However, investigators have not 
determined which driver ran the red light. 
</P>
