<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; HARBOR TAXI SERVICE SETS SAIL SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Penny and Ralph Rodheim want you to know that a taxicab isn't just a vehicle 
confined to land. This weekend they will start up a "Harbor Hopper" boat 
service to ferry passengers throughout Newport Harbor, stopping at Balboa 
Island, various restaurants along Mariners Mile, and along the Lido Peninsula 
and Lido Isle. 
</P>
<P>
 "I definitely think that it's something needed," Penny Rodheim said. "We don't 
often take advantage of so many things to do right here in the harbor. It makes 
everything more accessible." 
</P>
<P>
 Their water taxi is set to begin operating Saturday, departing from Balboa 
Boat Rentals on the Balboa Peninsula every hour and a half from noon until 
midnight. The boat will operate from noon until 9 p.m. on Sundays, noon until 6 
p.m. on Mondays, and 6 p.m. to midnight on Thursdays and Fridays. The boat 
carries 24 passengers. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rodheims said they hope their $12 all-day trips and $6 one-hour excursions 
will bring more business to local restaurants. Local restaurateurs welcomed the 
news, but said people have tried the same taxi idea in the past without notable 
success. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, cars are ferried from the peninsula to Balboa Island. The Harbor 
Hopper will take only people, and will cruise the shoreline as well as the 
island. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rodheims said they will try out the Harbor Hopper through the summer, and 
will continue the service if it is successful. LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
