<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eleven schools in the Placentia-Yorba Linda Unified School District will have 
new principals this fall. 
</P>
<P>
 The changes are part of the district's plan to rotate principals every five 
years, a policy adopted to allow school administrators to work at a variety of 
schools. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials also announced that they would conduct a job search for 
three principals to replace El Dorado High School Principal JoAnn Ball and Rose 
Drive Elementary School Principal Audell Jackson, who are retiring at the end 
of this school year, and Yorba Linda Middle School Principal Ken Lorge, who 
will become the district's administrator of child welfare and attendance. 
</P>
<P>
 The new principal assignments include Joe Quartucci, El Dorado High School; 
George Allen, Valencia High School; Richard Vouga, Yorba Linda Middle School; 
Randi Trontz, Morse Avenue Elementary School; Paula Emry-Burtt, Brookhaven 
Elementary School; Phil Hergenreder, Rose Drive Elementary School; Kathy 
Pritchard, Topaz Elementary School; and Kjell Taylor, Rio Vista Elementary 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, new principals will be hired at Esperanza High School, Travis 
Ranch School and Bernardo Yorba Middle School. DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
