<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; STANTON MAN HELD IN MOLESTATION CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's authorities have arrested a 44-year-old Stanton man on suspicion of 
molesting two teen-age boys he befriended while running a baseball card shop 
near Magnolia High School in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators arrested Luis Daniel Garcia on Friday on suspicion of child 
molestation and sexual exploitation of a child, Lt. Dan Martini reported 
Wednesday.The suspect is being held at Orange County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Martini said investigators believe there could be other victims, and ask 
anyone with information to call the Sheriff's Department Sex Crimes Unit at 
(714) 647-7479. Garcia, who has lived in Orange County for 20 years, may have 
been a coach in local baseball leagues, Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 The alleged molestation of the two boys, identified only as ages 14 and 15, 
occurred in Stanton and Westminster from 1992 to the present, Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 After befriending the boys at the baseball card shop, Martini said Garcia 
allegedly invited them to his Stanton apartment to view sexually explicit 
videos and magazines. The suspect allegedly molested the boys and recorded some 
of the acts on video without their knowledge, Martini said.ANNA CEKOLA 
</P>
</TEXT>
