<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; SECOND OF TWO MEN SHOT IN APRIL DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The second of two men shot April 29 in the 400 block of South Shelton Street 
has died, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Guadalupe Acosta, 20, of Santa Ana, who was shot several times while standing 
on the street with a friend, died Monday night, police Lt. Robert Helton said. 
Acosta had been hospitalized at UCI Medical Center in Orange since the 
shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Acosta's friend Francisco Miramontes, 25, of Laguna Hills, died May 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Miramontes and Acosta were standing in front of an apartment complex when they 
were confronted by a group of men, police said. Both were shot several times in 
the lower body. 
</P>
<P>
 Helton said the investigation of the shootings is continuing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
