<P>
 The Angels, determining that left fielder Dwight Smith is expendable, have had 
trade discussions that would send him to the Baltimore Orioles for left-handed 
reliever Brad Pennington, according to highly placed sources. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Orioles are trying to talk the Angels into players other than 
Pennington. 
</P>
<P>
 While the Orioles continue to balk about trading Pennington, sources say, 
another team has inquired about Smith. 
</P>
