before a decision is made on his fate. Farrell, 1-2 with a 9.00 earned-run 
average, probably will start some time next week, although Manager Marcel 
Lachemann said that it's still possible the start could come Sunday. Starting 
pitcher Brian Anderson, who pitched in rehabilitation Wednesday for Class-A 
Lake Elsinore, will throw on the side this weekend and join the rotation next 
week. . . . The Angels turned down Cleveland's request for an Aug. 15 makeup 
date and will play a doubleheader Sept. 2 in Cleveland to make up for Tuesday's 
rainout. . . . Angel reliever Scott Lewis underwent an examination on his sore 
shoulder and will have a bone scan. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
