<P>
DODGERS TO PAY STRAWBERRY $4,857,143 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Dodgers will make a lump-sum payment of $4,857,143 to Darryl Strawberry by 
July 1, according to the terms of their May 25 settlement, The Times has 
learned. 
</P>
<P>
 This amount consists of the balance of his 1994 salary, or $2,357,143, and 
half of the $5 million due him for next season, which was the final year of his 
five-year, $20.25-million contract. 
</P>
<P>
 Strawberry could clear 10-day release waivers Friday, making him a free agent. 
MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
