<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACLU TO APPEAL RULING ON KNIVES AT SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Civil Liberties Union announced Tuesday that it will appeal a 
federal judge's ruling that Livingston schools do not have to let Sikh students 
wear knives called kirpans. 
</P>
<P>
 Baptized Sikhs must wear kirpans as part of their religious tradition. But 
U.S. District Judge Garland E. Burrell of Sacramento ruled Friday that the 
ceremonial knives would impose an undue disruption of the district's schools 
and students. 
</P>
