<HEADLINE>
<P>
GET OUT THOSE COMFY SHOES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Other upcoming Cajun-zydeco events: 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday and Sunday, 11 a.m. to 7 p.m.: The 1994 Southern California Cajun & 
Zydeco Festival at the Rainbow Lagoon, next to the Long Beach Convention 
Center. Acts include D.L. Menard & the Louisiana Aces, Walter Mouton & the 
Scott Playboys, Steve Riley & the Mamou Playboys, Nathan & the Zydeco Cha-Chas, 
the Poullard Brothers and Joe Simien & Lisa Haley.Also, food booths and dance, 
music and cultural workshops. Single-day tickets are $14.50, two-day tickets 
are $27 in advance; $17 per day at the gate. Walter Mouton & the Scott Playboys 
and Nathan & the Zydeco Cha-Chas headline a dance Saturday night from 8 to 
midnight at the Convention Center Ballroom. $8 advance or $10 at the door. 
Information available from Comprehensive Child Development in Long Beach, which 
helps produce the festival and will receive some proceeds: (310) 427-3713. 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday, 8 p.m.: Queen Ida & the Bon Temps Zydeco Band play in the 
gymnasium at Saddleback College, 28000 Marguerite Parkway, Mission Viejo. Food 
fair starts 5:30 p.m. in the courtyard. $10 for Queen Ida, reservations 
recommended. Food fair benefits Angels, the college's arts support group. (714) 
582-4656. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Bon Temps Social Club of Orange County will sponsor dances on June 17 at 
the Culver City Masonic Hall, 9635 Venice Blvd., Culver City, and on July 29 at 
the Ebell Club of Anaheim, 226 N. Helena St., Anaheim. Doors open at 7 p.m., 
dance lessons at 7:30 p.m.; band plays 8 to 11 p.m. $8 to $10. ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
