<P>
PROSECUTOR CONVICTED OF BEATING A WITNESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former prosecutor was given a suspended prison sentence Wednesday for 
beating a witness during questioning in a major bribery scandal. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tokyo District Court sentenced Hitoshi Kanazawa, 33, to two years in 
prison but suspended the sentence for four years, meaning he can avoid prison 
by maintaining a clean record during that time. 
</P>
<P>
 Kanazawa was accused of slapping and kicking a 57-year-old executive during 
questioning Oct. 14 about bribes paid by construction executives to local 
politicians. 
</P>
