<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: LONG BEACH; REDUCTION IN BIXBY PARK TRAFFIC PROPOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EMILY ADAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council wants to close Bixby Park to through traffic during rush 
hours and thus reduce the number of drivers who cut through the park and nearby 
neighborhoods to avoid busy Ocean Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Under a proposal introduced by Councilmen Alan S. Lowenthal and Douglas S. 
Drummond, park gates at 1st Street and Cherry Avenue and 2nd Street and 
Junipero Avenue would be closed from 4 p.m. to 9 a.m. on weekdays.Currently, 
those gates are closed from 10 p.m. to 5 a.m. every day. 
</P>
<P>
 The council voted 7-1 last week to ask the city attorney to draw up an 
ordinance that would expand the hours that the park would be closed to through 
traffic. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Evan Anderson Braude opposed the new hours, saying he was denied a 
similar request to block traffic in his downtown district. Councilwoman Doris 
Topsy-Elvord was absent. EMILY ADAMS 
</P>
</TEXT>
