<P>
OFFICIALS SEIZE ASSETS OF INSURANCE BROKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 State insurance regulators said Wednesday they have seized the assets of an 
Irvine auto and truck insurance broker that they allege was selling policies 
without a license and channeling the premiums to other unlicensed firms. 
</P>
<P>
 Department of Insurance investigators said they acted last week against KD 
Excess & Surplus Insurance Services and the two companies to which it allegedly 
sent premiums: CFG Insurance Co. and CFG Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 KD Excess also collected premiums for a third insurer, Atlas Insurance Co., 
then diverted the premiums into CFG accounts in Nevada, state regulators said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Department of Insurance said it revoked KD Excess' license last July and 
also barred Atlas from doing business in California. 
</P>
<P>
 No one could be reached for comment Wednesday at KD Excess' Irvine office. 
</P>
