</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SPI Turns to PR: SPI Pharmaceuticals in Costa Mesa said Wednesday it has hired 
public relations agency Edelman Medical Communications of New York to give its 
products higher visibility in the scientific community. In particular, SPI 
said, it wants to promote its leading drug, Virazole. 
</P>
<P>
 The drug -- which is sold in 60 countries for treatment of various illnesses, 
including hepatitis C -- is approved for a single use in the United States: as 
an aerosol to treat infants hospitalized with severe viral respiratory 
infections. 
</P>
<P>
 ICN Pharmaceuticals, which owns a substantial stake in SPI, announced recently 
that it will seek federal approval to sell Virazole in this country to treat 
hepatitis C. The disease, which can go undetected for many years, destroys 
liver function. 
</P>
