<TEXT>
<P>
 Corollary Inc.: The Irvine-based maker of advanced computing equipment said 
Wednesday that a deal it signed with IBM for its communications technology is 
worth $10 million in the first year of the contract. It said IBM acquired 
marketing rights for its Corollary Connection Station, a computer that allows 
different kinds of computer networks to communicate quickly. 
</P>
